Comparative Analysis of Successful and Failed Enterprise System Implementations

Case Study 1: Successful Enterprise System Implementation
b.1. Company Overview
Company Name: Cisco Systems
Reason for Implementation: Cisco needed an enterprise resource planning (ERP) system to support its rapid growth, streamline operations, and replace its outdated legacy systems, which could no longer handle increasing transaction volumes.
b.2. Implementation Process
Cisco partnered with Oracle to deploy a new ERP system in just nine months, following a well-structured and phased implementation approach. The company invested heavily in training and change management, ensuring employee buy-in and seamless integration with existing processes.
